column5: Of course. There’s a lot of us out here going through the same thing. I feel like a different person now (in a good way) I can go out and not have the slightest hint of aniexty. Like there’s stated this med might not work out but there are a lot more. You’ll find the right one and happiness as well. Just takes time.

I’m on it (25mg) . Started on 11/25/19. My side effects lasted for 2 weeks or so. I had increased aniexty, diarrhea, tiredness and it was  hard to get to sleep at night. Nothing that was unbearable. A lot of people say it makes it worse before it gets better which Id agree with but I just stuck through it and at this point I’m glad I did.
Sorry to hear that. Hopefully not much longer for you.
I just talked to my regular  doctor. Told him how I was feeling and he recommended meds. Anxiety is a pretty common thing anymore.

I was the exact same way. I have health and social aniexty and I hated the idea Of medicine and only took aspirin or NyQuil. I had a doctors appt for abdominal pain and figured I’d throw in the aniexty since it had been bothering me pretty bad lately. Stomach pain was from aniexty and I got my prescription of Zoloft. It scared the crap out of me but my quality of life was declining so I gave it a shot. To start off positive. I feel like I’m in somebody else’s body, a normal person. I still get anxious thoughts but my body doesn’t respond like it used to. Events that used to cause borderline panic attacks are now walks in the park. As others have stated the first couple weeks are rough. But so worth the feeling of normalcy after. They are not for everyone and it may take a couple to find the right med or dose. For me though this was the right choice and I’m so much happier with life.

I was more or less the same way. Medication scared the crap out of me. I would lay awake at night worrying about scenarios that hadn’t happened. It started to get so bad I would leave work. I decided dealing with it on my own wasn’t working. I’m now on day 10 of meds (zoloft) and although the first week was rough I feel great now. I still get anxious thoughts but my body doesn’t react to them and they pass. Sounds weird but I feel normal now. I have health and social aniexty. At the very least talk to a medical professional about it. Medication isn’t for everybody and we all react different to meds. But for me this was the right decision. Feel free to message me if you have you need to talk or have any questions. There’s a lot of us out here, so you never have to feel alone.
